---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About | Pong News" description="Pong News is the first website dedicated to the science of table tennis and health.">
  <div class="about-page">

    <h1 class="about-page__title">About Pong News</h1>

    <div class="prose about-page__prose">
      <p><strong>Pong News</strong> is the first website dedicated to the science of table tennis and health. Every article on this site is based on peer-reviewed scientific research published in reputable medical and sports science journals.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Why this exists -->
    <div class="about-standout">
      <h2 class="about-standout__title">Why This Site Exists</h2>
      <p>Table tennis is one of the most popular sports in the world, played by an estimated 300+ million people globally. Yet most players have no idea about the extraordinary scientific evidence showing that this sport can extend life, prevent dementia, strengthen bones, and transform aging.</p>
      <p><strong>Nobody is aggregating this research.</strong> Studies are scattered across dozens of journals, locked behind paywalls, and written in dense academic language. Pong News bridges that gap — making the science accessible, accurate, and actionable.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Methodology -->
    <div class="about-methodology">
      <h2 class="about-section__title">Our Methodology</h2>
      <p class="prose">Every article follows a rigorous research process:</p>
      <ul class="about-methodology__list">
        <li class="about-methodology__item">
          <span class="about-methodology__marker">01</span>
          <span>We search PubMed, Google Scholar, and major journal databases for peer-reviewed studies on table tennis and health outcomes</span>
        </li>
        <li class="about-methodology__item">
          <span class="about-methodology__marker">02</span>
          <span>Every health claim links to a specific peer-reviewed study with journal name, publication year, and authors</span>
        </li>
        <li class="about-methodology__item">
          <span class="about-methodology__marker">03</span>
          <span>We report effect sizes and statistical significance, not just "studies show"</span>
        </li>
        <li class="about-methodology__item">
          <span class="about-methodology__marker">04</span>
          <span>We never exaggerate findings beyond what the data supports</span>
        </li>
        <li class="about-methodology__item">
          <span class="about-methodology__marker">05</span>
          <span>We clearly distinguish between correlation and causation</span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- What we cover -->
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 class="about-section__title">What We Cover</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Longevity:</strong> Life expectancy data, mortality reduction, aging biomarkers</li>
          <li><strong>Cognitive Health:</strong> Alzheimer's, dementia, BDNF, neuroplasticity, brain structure</li>
          <li><strong>Physical Health:</strong> Bone density, balance, fall prevention, cardiovascular fitness</li>
          <li><strong>Rehabilitation:</strong> Parkinson's, stroke recovery, motor control, therapy</li>
          <li><strong>Mental Health:</strong> Depression, anxiety, social isolation, quality of life</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Credibility -->
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 class="about-section__title">Our Standards</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <ul>
          <li>Every health claim is traced to a specific peer-reviewed study</li>
          <li>We cite journal names, publication years, and lead authors</li>
          <li>We report effect sizes and statistical significance</li>
          <li>We never overstate findings or cherry-pick data</li>
          <li>We distinguish between observational and experimental evidence</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Contact -->
    <div class="about-section">
      <h2 class="about-section__title">Get in Touch</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>Have a study we should cover? Want to contribute? Spot an error in our reporting?</p>
        <p>Reach us at <strong>hello@pongnews.com</strong></p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</Layout>
